Uddevalla h. a. 1. 32-36, musiklär. v. Falköp. samrealsk. sed. 36, organist o. kantor i Falköp. kyrka sed. s. å. Dirig. f. Falköp. orik:fören. sed. 36. Komp.: Kantat (39). P. A. Bergs jeton.
translated: Bartler, Jens Anders, music director, Falköping, born August 24, 1907 in Hudiksvall. Married in 1938 to dentist Ingrid Agner. Children: Göran born in 1940, Gunilla born in 1943. He achieved the degree of organist in 1929, music teacher in 1930, and cantor in 1931, all from the Music Conservatory in Stockholm. He studied in Berlin and Leipzig in 1934 and in France in 1937. He was a teacher at the high school in Uddevalla from 1932-1936, and a music teacher at the Falköping secondary school since 1936. He has been an organist and cantor in the Falköping church since the same year and has been the conductor for the Falköping choral society since 1936. His compositions include a cantata from 1939 and he was awarded the P. A. Berg medal.
